(42, 8, 29, 41, 9, 20, 26, 'driven of the devil into the wilderness', 'Connection of Demonic Affliction', 'Both passages emphasize the severe torment caused by unclean spirits. The man in Luke is driven into the wilderness, while the child in Mark is cast into fire and water, showcasing the destructive nature of these spirits.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 29, 42, 9, 39, 39, 'driven of the devil into the wilderness', 'Connection of Demonic Affliction', 'Both passages emphasize the torment caused by unclean spirits. The first describes a man driven into the wilderness by a spirit, while the second depicts a boy suffering from a spirit that tears him and causes foaming at the mouth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 29, 44, 19, 12, 16, NULL, 'Evil Spirits and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of evil spirits and the struggle against them. In Luke, the unclean spirit is driven into the wilderness, while in Acts, the evil spirits respond to authority, highlighting the power dynamics involved in exorcism.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 29, 55, 2, 25, 26, NULL, 'Connection of Spiritual Captivity', 'Both passages emphasize being ''taken captive'' by the devil. Luke describes a man bound by an unclean spirit, while 2 Timothy speaks of those caught in the devil''s snare. This connection highlights the theme of spiritual bondage and the need for deliverance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
